‚úçÔ∏è Recommended workflow

  • Set picture size to 540x960 (for portraits) or 960x540 (for landscapes). Don't go above 1024px!

  • Put nationality into positive prompt, for example (Irish girl:1.3) or (Malaysian woman:1.3) to modify face shape and skin tone.

  • Use negative embeddings or good negative prompt. You can find popular embeddings here

  • Use Lora's for better image quality (read below)

  • (optional) Put age into positive prompt. Be specific. Use keywords like: XX years old, girl, woman, old lady, elderly woman.

    photography of German girl, 20 years old

For tests you can use sd-dynamic-prompts and this prompt.
For best results use Clip Skip 1 and keep in mind that prompting nationalities may affect clothes and backgrounds (if you don't specify them by yourself).

items.name: Ibis Crystal sub-LoRA
items.description:
This sub-LoRA is suitable for combination with other LoRAs to give shine and crystal structure. Alone, the results of crystal LoRA can look strange and resemble crumpled spotted paper.

Warning: sub-LoRA's work alone may look strange. Don't treat it as a full-fledged style. It was created SPECIFICALLY for transparent styles.

Sub-LoRA works well with mods of water, crystals, glass and other translucent materials. The image becomes more smoothed, textured and pleasing to the eye. The faces appear partially transparent, giving more realism to the generation of crystalline or translucent creatures.

With opaque materials, it can impart texture as in three-dimensional computer games.

The only thing is that the dataset is trained mainly on alien plants and female faces, so if you don't write clarifying words, pants and girls will most often be generated.

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

I.Overview of the model:

To this day, we still miss the continent of Azeroth; vaguely remember that 10 years ago, I chose the Necromancer and started a journey to World of Warcraft; once upon a time, in order to complete a series of achievements, I forgot to eat and sleep, in order to form a team Set the alarm clock regularly in the next copy, in order to catch a baby mount, squatting all night... The original intention of training this model is to commemorate the passing green years. All training materials come from Internet pictures, game screenshots, etc.; you can try to use This model generates a picture as a wallpaper, look through it occasionally, and commemorate your World of Warcraft.

II.The model use instructions:

1, Recommended lora weight: 0.7-0.9, add trigger word: wow2wow.

2, Recommended to load the base large model: ReV Animated_v1.2.2.

3, The number of iteration steps: 25-40, CFG scale: 10-15, Clip skip: 2.

4, Recommended sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras.

5, VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.

6, For the resolution settings, the recommended horizontal version: 768x512 (or 960x768), vertical cell phone size: 512x768 (or 768x960), after getting the above picture, you can subsequently use HD repair (redrawing amplitude 0.3-0.4, zoom algorithm R-ESRGAN 4x +) zoom 2 times to increase the rich picture details; of course, you can also choose Instead of HD restoration, you can use Tiled Diffusion + Tiled VAE to enlarge the image, which will give you a better quality image.

7, The generalization of this model is not bad, and it can produce pictures under different base models; for example, switch to a real-style or animation-style large model to generate some interesting pictures, friends can try.

III. Other notes:

1, Warcraft lora standard short call words:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

wow2wow,<lora:wow2wow:0.9>.

darkness,star \(sky\), weapon,glowing.

masterpiece, best quality, most detailed, best aesthetics, highest contrast, highest resolution, best details, 8K wallpapers,

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Load lora directly, add the trigger word:wow2wow, and then with some prompt words you can get some pictures of scenes and characters in the World of Warcraft style type.

2, Some other recommended prompt words:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

darkness,weapon,star\(sky\),glowing,android,robot,fantasy,landscape,waterfall,tree,knight,helmet,cloudy sky,outdoors,male focus. snowing,mountain, floating island, cloud, scenery, sky, day, 1girl, no humans, fire,nature, sword, castle, armor, cape, forest, lantern, grass, water, light rays, flower. sunlight, bridge, fantasy, house,villages, rivers, buildings, etc.Some prompt words related to Warcraft style,you can try them all;

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Guys, try different cue words out of the map (Recommended combinations of 2-8 prompt words), without copying all the above cue words into Stable Diffusion, to try some interesting combinations of play to generate different pictures similar to the World of Warcraft style.

3, Recommended negative cue words:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NSFW,(ng_deepnegative_v1_75t:1.5),(easynegative:1.5),(worst quality:2),(low quality:2),(normal quality:2),lowres,low resolution,bad anatomy,bad hands,extra fingers,missing finger,missing fingers,bad feet,extra feet,((monochrome)),((grayscale)),watermark,number

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4, In view of the limited original materials of this model V1.0, if you only use the same model to generate pictures, the generated pictures will not have too many patterns. You can try to switch different base models to change the style (for example, anime style model: Counterfeit-V3. 0), it is also interesting to experience more Warcraft-style scenes and characters obtained by loading different bottom models; later, when I have time, I will continue to iterate and supplement training to improve this model,

5, Please note: this model does not generate the original Warcraft picture, copyright issues we all understand, needless to say, only similar style images of Warcraft can be generated, if you need commercial use, please be careful.

6, Regarding the use of this model, everyone is welcome to map feedback;If there are any questions about the use of Stable Diffusion and model training (alchemy), you can communicate together, we play AI painting together and progress together.

items.name: Daniela - Hentai University
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Daniela, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Daniela's art is from the artist Oreteki18kin, the set -

Futaba-chan Jusei Chu‚òÜ

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times. These (and the rest of the gym girls) especially only have about 15 images to work from each, and they're not ideal images. It still works, but it takes more finagling that some of the other characters for sure.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUDaniela
Recommended tags - purple hair, brown eyes, medium hair, scrunchie, medium breasts, twintails,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: CPU_Die_v2
items.description:
Trained on lots of photos of CPU/GPU dies shots, from chips by Nvidia, AMD, Intel and Apple.

I think CPU/GPU dies are the most beautiful images of technology I've ever seen. Did you know the rainbow of colors are an effect of how they reflect light? I used to think it was just advertising, but it's not.

Everyone is so focused on portraits and landscapes, but if you support me, I will make more LoRAs like this, which are good in portraits and landscapes too, but excellent in abstract design and technology-themed art.

If you use this model for commercial work, please consider buying me a coffee, or better yet, help me get a graphics card with more than 12GB VRAM, so I can train better models! It takes a lot of time and effort to make these kinds of LoRAs, such as editing the dataset images and running multiple epochs.

Also, please post what you make with this, so people will see what to do with them.

modelVersions.name: CPU_Die_v2
modelVersions.description:
Version 1 was trained on 512x512 images that were scaled down from HUGE images, but garbage in, garbage out and detail was lacking in the model. Version 2 was an all new model trained on 1024x1024 chunks of the original images. Some were over 8000 pixels per side!

Most of the dataset images were HUGE (over 5000 pixels per side), so I cut them up into bite (byte?)-size chunks, so no detail was lost. This was a huge improvement over version 1, which were just scaled down versions. The details are much more crisp, now. I also trained on the largest images I could (1024x1024).

items.name: RealCartoon3D
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Updates: 9/11/23 - Uploaded version 8! Had some time to play around :)

RealCartoon3D is my first model uploaded. The reason for the upload was to share the fruit of trying to get a checkpoint to do what I wanted it to do when prompted. Some goals for this checkpoint were as follows:

  • 1. Variety in humans (I.E. African, European, Asian, etc). I did not want it just producing the same look I saw everywhere.

  • 2. Produce realistic flaws in skin (just adds to the realism).

  • 3. Do well with LoRAs.

The mission was/is to attempt to get this checkpoint to a point where it will do well on first attempt or second attempt with prompts (my computer is just a gaming laptop that gets really hot when doing things like this lol).

I have learned a lot in the process and even started other checkpoints (RealCartoon-Anime, Realistic, Pixar) to give a more focused variation. This checkpoint being the basis for all of them. I always keep this one merged in all the updates of the others.

I hope you all enjoy it! Please review and share your images. I very much appreciate the support with the downloads and feedback (THANK YOU ALL). Never thought it would get this much attention.

The Process:


The starting checkpoints for merging were a couple of top ones of course (The checkpoints do/did not have restrictions on checkpoint mergers. These are in my recommended resources as well). I also baked in the VAE (vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned). I tried ClearVAE, but it would mess up from time to time (which may have been my computer). I did not want this issue to fall to anyone that downloaded this model, so I did not use that VAE. Sadly, I did not have the resources to train from scratch; but found that many people would just train off these checkpoints anyway. As time moved on, I would try to find checkpoints that had a look or cool backdrop (or odd result sometimes) that would help the overall look (again avoiding those that had restrictions with merging, as I do not want to mess up anyone's work or get lost in licensing). One issue that would always seem to show up was hands being messed up. They just did not come out right (as many checkpoints seemed to have a problem with); but as I kept moving forward in merging, the hands seemed to get better. I would then look for LoRas to influence the look and style (Ones used are in the resource section). These LoRas were not to take over the checkpoint but help mold it per say. As I wanted the user to have control of this. Since that is the point of LoRas.

Overall, this checkpoint moved up in versions quickly as it got figured out. Eventually it started to really go where I wanted with Version 3.0, 3.1, and then of course Version 4 (slowing down a bit in the updates as well). I still like the older versions; and they did influence the RealCartoon-Pixar and Anime directions.

The Settings:

  • Width: 512 (normally would not adjust unless I flipped the height and width)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 1024, but 768 was my sweet spot)

  • Sampling Method: "Eular A" became pretty much the default as versions moved along, but "DPM++ SDE Karra" and "DPM++ 2M Karras" are favorites for me as well.

  • Sampling steps: 30-50 normally (30 being my starting point, but going up to 45 a lot of the time)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4k-UltraSharp most of the time), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (1.5 or 2 does well)

  • Clip Skip: 2

Would run ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but many times in the later versions I would not run this as it was not needed.

Some settings I run on the web-Ui to help get the images without crashing:

set COMMANDLINE_ARGS=--opt-sdp-no-mem-attention --lowvram --opt-split-attention --xformers

Why So Many Versions:

Because I wanted to share all the results that I felt reached a desired outcome. Allowed me to have fun, and I saw that many enjoyed them. Which motivated me to keep trying. Again, thank you.

Again, I try to get them to hit on the first try as much as possible; and this version seemed like it was doing that really well. modelVersions.name: V6

modelVersions.name: V5
modelVersions.description: Ok, so I loved how Version 4 turned out. It also looks like many liked it as well, BUT I received some feedback that it was not doing "older" women very well. Tested it out a bit with some LoRAs it would not make more "mature" women. Men it did fine though. So, the challenge was to get that information into the model without losing the look. So, here is version 5. It does not move far from version 4; but it does do older MUCH better. :)

modelVersions.name: V4
modelVersions.description:
I was working on RealCartoon-Pixar and RealCartoon-Realistic and just felt my base model that started it all needed some love. So, after some many mixes and adjustments (and my computer not liking me in the process) I can now present version 4. This version responds very well to prompts and seems like it handles hands a bit better (but messes up from time to time like most models lol). Overall, I have really enjoyed the details this version produces.

I hope you all enjoy!! Also, thank you all for your reviews and likes!! I really appreciate the support!

modelVersions.name: V3.1
modelVersions.description: After some fun working on the Anime and Realistic versions, I was playing around with the base one again. I ended up with this version that I feel does very well in the details and overall response to the prompts, while keeping to what I want RealCartoon3D to be doing. I loved it and felt it needed to be shared. So, here is 3.1 of RealCartoon3D. I hope you all enjoy and continue to share your images. Please rate as well!! I should be getting the pruned version up tomorrow or so. CiVitai has been up and down so, we shall see.

modelVersions.name: V3.0
modelVersions.description:
This Version should be the final. At least for the direction this model is going. This version hits a happy medium (at least for me) between realistic and cartoon. Love the variety and types of people it can create, along with having a good range of prompt ability. I hope you share your images. I really enjoy seeing the results. Please rate as well!! Keeps me motivated to do this. :)

All the samples for this version were done pretty much on Euler A. Just playing with that sampling method at the moment. ADetailer was not enabled for them as well. Still came out rather nicely.

Thank you all for the likes and downloads. I will be uploading an anime version as well soon, but it will be under the Name: RealCartoon-Anime.

modelVersions.name: V2.5
modelVersions.description: Ok, so this version is trying to find that balance; to get to what I am going to be calling my final version (3.0) of this model (unless I just get some wow moment in playing around). I want to take two paths with this model. One will lean more towards an anime look and the other towards a real look. So this model (RealCartoon3D) will be the middle ground. This 2.5 Version just had some really nice results, and I wanted to share them. Again, all the version actually do very well; but I am striving for one that just gets it all (for the middle ground that is). :) Hope you all enjoy!!
